article.headline: Temple 77, Rutgers 54
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Dionte Christmas scored a career-high 27 points to lead Temple to a 77-54 victory over Rutgers on Wednesday night for the Owls' first win under new head coach Fran Dunphy. Temple (1-2) blew the game open with a 31-7 run over a 12-minute stretch that spanned both halves. Christmas capped the onslaught with 12 straight points, and his final bucket in that string gave the Owls a 52-26 lead with 14:12 left. DaShone Kirkendoll added a career-high 20 points, going 6-for-7 from beyond the 3-point arc. As a team, Temple shot 63 percent (12-for-19) from 3-point range, with Christmas making five of his six attempts. Temple had lost its first two games under Dunphy, the longtime University of Pennsylvania head coach who replaced John Chaney when the Hall of Famer retired in March. Dion Dacons set a career high with 10 rebounds and Chris Clark provided a spark off the bench, finishing with seven assists. Rutgers (1-5) continued to struggle under new head coach Fred Hill and has yet to beat a Division I opponent this season, their only win coming against Division II St. Thomas Aquinas. JR Inman, who has scored in double digits in every game this season, led Rutgers with 12 points and nine rebounds, while Adrian Hill and Anthony Farmer each finished with 11. The Scarlet Knights shot just 33 percent (19-for-57) and only 18 percent (4-for-22) from 3-point range.
